BACKGROUND:
Sample Nodes:
recipe_list (recipes generated from spoonacular API using specific ingredient names from FoodOn and Ingredient graph datasets)


READ:
1) Create Spoonacular API account (https://rapidapi.com/spoonacular/api/recipe-food-nutrition/), subscribe in pricing, and generate python code for get/random recipes or download all files from google drive link (https://drive.google.com/drive/folders/1D2X71lQ1xLab-ITnTsRB6OTWZEYH3A4p?usp=sharing).
2) Run JSON to CSV Converter (https://www.convertcsv.com/json-to-csv.htm) to convert json to csv files.
3) Create neo4j database and change settings/configuration with the following:
dbms.memory.heap.initial_size=30G
dbms.memory.heap.max_size=30G 
dbms.memory.pagecache.size=1G
4) Run edit_spoonacular.ipynb to edit certain columns from csv files.
5) Import csv files in neo4j database import folder and run following neo4j cypher in browser:
#Create Recipe List Nodes
#Recipe List 1 (All Purpose Flour)
CREATE CONSTRAINT recipelistIdConstraint ON (recipelist:RecipeList) ASSERT recipelist.id IS UNIQUE
:auto USING PERIODIC COMMIT 500
LOAD CSV WITH HEADERS FROM "file:///spoonacular_recipe_list_1.csv" AS csvLine
CREATE (rl:RecipeList {vegetarian: toBoolean(csvLine.vegetarian),
 vegan: toBoolean(csvLine.vegan),

:auto USING PERIODIC COMMIT 500
